key_points: California is issuing another round of stimulus checks to eligible residents.
Around 750,000 paper checks began distribution on November 1, and 400,000 payments were direct deposited on October 29.
The total value of these payments exceeds $857 million.
The Golden State Stimulus II checks started being sent out in late August.
Eligible residents include those who filed a 2020 state income tax return by October 15, 2021, earned $75,000 or less, and cannot be claimed as a dependent.
Eligibility also requires having a Social Security or an Individual Taxpayer Identification Number.
Direct deposit payments may take several days, while paper checks distribution depends on the recipient's zip code.
The expected completion of stimulus check distribution spans into early next year.
An estimated nine million Californians are poised to receive the stimulus checks.
Residents can use an online tool provided by California to check their payment eligibility.
